    "If the capability is valid, the content and the interest will be forwarded otherwise, it will be discarded.",
    "In the proposed scheme the authors designed a lightweight one-time signature scheme for CSEA to certify the correctness of content and support efficient verification.",
    "Moreover, the given scheme can prevent different types of attacks such as content poisoning attacks, DoS attacks, and content leakage attacks.",
    "However, the given scheme requires a lot of changes in NDN architecture.",
    "In addition, the scheme is affected by the issues of latency and extra overhead due to the addition of tokens with every interest and content."
